CAIRO, Dec. 16 (Xinhua) -- Arab League (AL) Secretary-General Ahmed Aboul-Gheit on Thursday discussed in Cairo with the visiting International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) Director General Rafael Mariano Grossi the nuclear issues in Iran and Israel, according to the AL's statement. Aboul-Gheit called on Israel to "join the Treaty on the Non-Proliferation of Nuclear Weapons and to put all its nuclear activities and facilities under the IAEA's supervision." The meeting also tackled the Iranian nuclear talk's latest developments. Aboul-Gheit highlighted that the concerns of the Arab countries over the Iranian nuclear deal should be considered. Enditem